messages.content: 9-1-1, what's your emergency?
Yes, this is Danelle Dash. I live over here by Carquest.
Okay.
It sounds like gunshots are being fired.
Okay. Do you know where they are coming from?
No, it was two different sets. The first set went off, and now we just heard the second set.
What is your address?
The man ran past Pac-Man's house.
Did he have a gun? Can you see what he had?
No, he just ran past.
What is your name, ma'am?
Danelle Dashlet. D-O-N-N-E-L-L.
I have Danelle Dashlet on the phone. She believes she heard gunshots near Carquest and saw a man run past Pac-Man's house.
A pickup truck just went down Hazeldale at high speed.
Okay.
Mr. Bob, get the kids down! My car's been shot. I had 3-23 rounds, came 7 meters from my head. They went through my squad. He is shooting down!
Ma'am, can I put you on hold for a second?
Yes.
Hey, Cullen, Fuller's calling 911. Shots are being fired, one went past my head and through my squad.
I'm going to put you on hold, ma'am.
Okay.
We need units in the pad now!
Your call has been forwarded to an automatic voice message system.
Can you see what's going on?
No, somebody in a black Toyota Tundra just peeled out of here.
Did you get a license number?
No, we are inside the house.
Which way did it go?
It went down Hazeldale towards Tyler's Ripper stand.
Okay, I'll put you back on hold again.
All units, be advised, we have a report of a black Toyota Tundra leaving Hazeldale area at high speed heading towards Tyler's drive-in after shots were fired.
Can you hear anything else?
No, it's been quiet here.
Okay, thank you.
There's someone standing on the porch at Hazeldale on the shooting.
Do they have a gun?
I can't tell, I'm at 206, it's kitty corner.
Do you know who it is?
No, but there are two Native Americans that live on the lower level. I'm not saying it's them. A black Chevy pickup left the Suburban there.
Did it leave at a high rate of speed?
Yes, it did.
Thank you, stay away from your windows.
We will.
Forest County 911, what's your emergency?
Yeah, we have a shooting outside our apartment building.
What's the address, ma'am?
Behind Trisha's Treasures at 107 North Lake Ave. Someone is sobbing and they need an ambulance.
Isn't that near the post office and city police?
Yes.
What is your name?
April Aubrey. We're in our apartment with the doors locked, looking out the window.
Stay away from the windows, April. An ambulance is on its way.
Okay, thank you.
Forest County 911, what's your emergency?
I don't know if it's cops or not, but someone's walking down the street with a rifle on Hazeldale.
Can you tell if it's an officer?
No, I can't.
Okay, thank you. We'll send someone to check it.
Forest County 911, what's your emergency?
My name is Robert Dashlett. My wife called earlier about the pickup truck.
Yes, we had many calls coming in at that time.
Do you need a description? It was a navy blue Chevy with a silver toolbox behind the cab.
Thank you. We have officers in the area.
Okay. There were around 20 shots fired, I think.
Thank you, Robert.
Forest County 911, what's your emergency?
This is Elder Pagel. Is it safe for my family? We've got a lot of people here and just want to be sure.
Elder, we recommend that everyone stays inside and uses their best judgment. We cannot release more information right now.
All right. Thank you.
Forest County 911, what's your emergency?
Yeah, a friend of mine said they saw Tyler driving a black Chevy with a silver toolbox on P near Argonne.
Do you know which way he was heading?
No, only that it was near Bud Isens' place on P.
Thank you, we'll notify the officers.
Forest County 911, may I help you?
This is Special Agent Jody Wormick from DCI. You can disregard the request for EMS or METFlight. The subject is down.
Thank you.
Forest County 911, what's your emergency?
This is Donna Dashlet. We are up here on County N. With all this commotion, should we evacuate our home?
We haven't received any evacuation orders. If you don't feel safe, you may leave, but there might be road closures.
Okay, thank you. Please keep us updated if anything changes.
We'll do our best. Stay safe.
Forest County 911, what's your emergency?
This is Phil McCorkal. My granddaughter Katrina was involved in the shooting this morning. Her car is now out here on Stetsney Lane. I don't know if the suspect is nearby.
Okay, we'll inform the officers. Thank you.
